Density = mass per unit volume: rho = m/V. Unit: kg m^{-3}.
Conversion: 1 g cm^{-3} = 1000 kg m^{-3}.

Typical values:
• Air: ~1.2 kg m^{-3}
• Water: 1000 kg m^{-3}
• Aluminium: 2700 kg m^{-3}
• Steel: 7800 kg m^{-3}

Density is a scalar, property of the material not the object.

Worked example: Cube side 0.1 m, mass 2.7 kg.
V = 0.001 m^3. rho = 2.7/0.001 = 2700 kg m^{-3} (aluminium).
